news.title: Single window system of Chennai development body for building approvals goes live
news.para: “Hopefully in 15 days’ time it would be open for all,” said Anshul Mishra, CMDA member-secretary. “Within a certain period the inspections are not completed, the application would be deemed approved and the onus would be on the official incharge,” he said.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Madhav Group buys Bodakdev plot for Rs 250 crore
news.para: Amit Patel, the principal promoter of Madhav Group, said, “We recently bought this plot and plan to launch a residential project on it. We will build a 30-32 storey residential building with about 260 apartments.”

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP directs builders to hand over upkeep plans to RWAs in 30 days
news.para: District town planner (enforcement) RS Batth said these documents are related to water supply, sewage, electricity, rainwater harvesting, stormwater drainage, fire services and lifts.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government to find why builders are filing for bankruptcy
news.para: Several big names of the real estate industry, including Amrapali, Jaypee Group, Three C Homes, Unitech and Sahara, have faced insolvency proceedings in the past.

news.title: China Vanke expects 2022 profit to stabilise
news.para: Vanke reported a net profit of 22.5 billion yuan ($3.54 billion) in 2021, down from 41.5 billion yuan in the year-ago period, dented by lower gross profit margins in the development business, a drop in investment income and the provision for asset impairment losses.

news.title: Maharashtra to start collecting 1% metro cess on property purchases from April 1
news.para: Bhushan Gagrani, principal secretary (urban development), said the state government had taken a decision in February 2019 to levy one per cent metro cess on property purchases in four cities including Mumbai.

news.title: China: CIFI Holdings to issue $250 million convertible bonds
news.para: The conversion price of the 6.95% bond due April 2025 is HK$5.53 per share, 20% higher than Thursday's closing price. If the bonds are fully converted, the shares represent 3.87% of the enlarged capital.

news.title: Australia housing bubble slowly deflating as heat leaves Sydney, Melbourne
news.para: Figures from property consultant CoreLogic out on Friday showed prices in the combined capital cities edged up only 0.3% in March, from February, as Sydney dropped 0.2% and Melbourne 0.1%.

news.title: U.S: Long-term mortgage rates rise again; 30-year breaches 4.5%
news.para: Mortgage buyer Freddie Mac reported Thursday that the average rate on the 30-year loan this week rose to 4.67% from 4.42% last week.

news.title: Maharashtra CM to inaugurate two new Mumbai Metro lines on April 2
news.para: Metro services on the first phase of Line 2A and also Line 7, both in western suburbs, will be thrown open for commuter use, Mumbai Metropolitan Region Development Authority (MMRDA) commissioner SVR Srinivas said.

news.title: CIDCO allotted 15,000 homes amid covid-19 pandemic
news.para: ​These include COVID warriors, police personnel, families in the low income group, people with disabilities (PwD) among others, an official said.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government sets January 2023 deadline for comprehensive land survey
news.para: The officials told chief minister YS Jagan Mohan Reddy at a review meeting at his Tadepalli camp office on Thursday that they were working to complete land survey and issue clear titles in 5,200 villages by the end of July 2023, 5,700 villages by the end of August 2023 and 6,460 villages by the end of September 2023.

news.title: Lying idle for 10 years, YEIDA takes back plots from firms
news.para: In total, the industrial authority took back around 2.2 lakh sqmt from the private developers and passed an order to forfeit Rs 27.3 crore that they had deposited.

news.title: Property registrations in Vizianagaram see marginal drop in FY22
news.para: The stamps and registration department which collects a percentage for registration of properties such as flats, houses, lands, and others is one of the top revenue contributors.

news.title: Haryana CM to hold round table meet on Global City project
news.para: According to officials, the land on which the Global City project is set to come up is a part of an area that had been transferred to Reliance Industries in 2006 to be developed as a special economic zone (SEZ).
